Part 2 of a comic I did for National Geographic.
The piece talks through many of the ways the American healthcare industry fails women.

Part 1 of a comic I did for National Geographic.
The piece talks through many of the ways the American healthcare industry fails women (dismissal of women’s pain, lack of research) and highlights the importance of individual stories and narratives as a way to create change.
Thanks to AD Marianne Sergi!

I did two illustrations and a one page comic for National Geographic.
The piece talks through many of the ways the American healthcare industry fails women (dismissal of women's pain, lack of research) and highlights the importance of individual stories and narratives as a way to create change. 
Huge thanks to AD Marianne Sergi!
